      • submit

        public static void submit(BulletStormConfig bulletConfig,
                          String recordComponent,
                          org.apache.storm.topology.TopologyBuilder builder,
                          org.apache.storm.Config stormConfig)
                   throws Exception
        This function can be used to wire up the source of the records to Bullet. The name of the last component in your topology and the TopologyBuilder used to create your topology should be provided. That topology will be wired up with Bullet reading from your component that produces the BulletRecord.
        Parameters:
        bulletConfig - The non-null, validated BulletStormConfig that contains the necessary configuration.
        recordComponent - The non-null name of the component used in your topology that is the source of records for Bullet.
        builder - The non-null TopologyBuilder that was used to create your topology.
        stormConfig - The non-null Storm Config to use to submit the topology with.
        Throws:
        Exception - if there were issues creating the topology.

      • submit

        public static void submit(BulletStormConfig bulletConfig,
                          org.apache.storm.topology.TopologyBuilder builder,
                          org.apache.storm.Config stormConfig)
                   throws Exception
        This submits a topology after loading the configured Spout (and optionally, Bolt), which is either the DSLSpout and DSLBolt or a custom Spout and Bolt. The topology is submitted with the given configuration as the source of BulletRecord using the given TopologyBuilder. Takes a Config if any custom settings were added.
        Parameters:
        bulletConfig - The Bullet settings for this Bullet topology.
        builder - The TopologyBuilder to use to add the topology to.
        stormConfig - The Storm Config to use for this topology.
        Throws:
        Exception - if there were any issues submitting the topology.
